nto the university setting. By showing the gains in campus capital these first-generation college students obtained through social media, the authors offer concrete suggestions for how other universities and college-retention programs can utilize the findings to increase their own retention of first-generation college students.    aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 4aacademic program. 4aacademics. 4acampus. 4acollege student. 4acollege. 4afacebook. 4ainternet. 4aonline. 4asocial media. 4ateachnology. 4atechnology. 4atwitter. 4auniversity. 4awebsite. 70(DE-601)1041236480(DE-588)4299541-3aHöheres Bildungswesen2gnd 70(DE-601)1060767870(DE-588)4078641-9aUnterrichtstechnologie2gnd 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh1 aAlemán, Ana M. Martínez, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut.1 aSavitz-Romer, Mandy, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Pilot eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311066330308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package 2017-2018z978311065742508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2018z978311066608340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813594231423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813594231.jpg  a978-3-11-065742-5  RUP eBook-Package 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066330-3  RUP Pilot eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-066608-3  RUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG